      "comment": "MYSTICAL MAN (7) proved too strong two runs ago at this track. Safely held last time out when fourth over 1600m at Marble Bar, beaten 3.5 lengths. Ideally placed and is sure to take plenty of stopping. STAR TESTYMONY (8) finished 4.5 lengths back in seventh when returning from a break and tackling a dirt track for the first time last start at Broome over 1780m. Sure to come on from that run and has winning claims. DYNAMIC ONE (1) met with solid support last start over 1200m at this track when eighth, beaten 5.5 lengths. Rosie Mahony who has scored on him two times retains the mount. One of the main contenders. ANOTHER NEPHEW (4) was a dominant winner last time over 1600m at Marble Bar, drifting well back but unleashing late to run away with a 2-length win. Can figure in the finish. REGINALD (3) is racing in good order and can't be left out of calculations.",
